        {
          "id": "q1",
          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Percentage", "difficulty": "medium"},
          "text": "60% of a number is 36 more than 40% of the same number. The number is:",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "160"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "180"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "200"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "240"}
          ],
          "answer": "B",
          "explanation": "20% of the number is 36, so it is 180."
        },
        {
          "id": "q2",
          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Profit & Loss", "difficulty": "medium"},
          "text": "The cost price of 12 articles equals the selling price of 10 articles. The profit percentage is:",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "16.67%"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "20%"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "25%"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "12%"}
          ],
          "answer": "B",
          "explanation": "SP/CP = 12/10, i.e. 20% profit."
        },
        {
          "id": "q3",
          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Discount + Profit & Loss", "difficulty": "hard"},
          "text": "An article marked at Rs 800 is sold after a discount of 12.5%. If the seller still gains 25%, the cost price is:",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "Rs 520"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "Rs 540"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "Rs 560"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "Rs 600"}
          ],
          "answer": "C",
          "explanation": "SP = 700; CP = 700/1.25 = 560."
        },
        {
          "id": "q4",
          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Time & Work", "difficulty": "medium"},
          "text": "A and B together can finish a work in 6 days. A alone can finish it in 10 days. B alone can finish it in:",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "12 days"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "15 days"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "16 days"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "18 days"}
          ],
          "answer": "B",
          "explanation": "1/6 - 1/10 = 1/15."
        },
        {
          "id": "q5",
          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Pipes & Cisterns", "difficulty": "medium"},
          "text": "A tap can fill a tank in 8 hours, while a leak can empty the full tank in 24 hours. With both open, the tank fills in:",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "10 hours"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "12 hours"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "14 hours"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "16 hours"}
          ],
          "answer": "B",
          "explanation": "1/8 - 1/24 = 1/12."
        },
        {
          "id": "q6",
          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Time & Distance (Average Speed)", "difficulty": "medium"},
          "text": "A car travels from town A to town B at 60 km/h and returns at 40 km/h. Its average speed for the whole journey is:",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "50 km/h"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "52 km/h"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "48 km/h"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "45 km/h"}
          ],
          "answer": "C",
          "explanation": "Average = 2xy/(x+y) = 4800/100 = 48."
        },
        {
          "id": "q7",
          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Time & Distance (Trains)", "difficulty": "easy"},
          "text": "A 180 m long train passes a pole in 12 seconds. Its speed is:",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "48 km/h"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "54 km/h"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "60 km/h"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "64 km/h"}
          ],
          "answer": "B",
          "explanation": "15 m/s = 54 km/h."
        },
        {
          "id": "q8",
          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Interest (CI vs SI)", "difficulty": "hard"},
          "text": "The difference between compound interest and simple interest on Rs 5000 at 8% per annum for 2 years is:",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "Rs 28"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "Rs 30"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "Rs 32"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "Rs 40"}
          ],
          "answer": "C",
          "explanation": "Difference = P(r/100)^2 = 5000 x 0.0064 = 32."
        },
        {
          "id": "q9",
          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Ratio & Proportion", "difficulty": "easy"},
          "text": "The third proportional to 8 and 12 is:",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "16"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "18"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "20"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "24"}
