          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Mixture & Alligation", "difficulty": "medium"},
          "text": "Rice at Rs 40/kg and Rs 55/kg is mixed to get a mixture worth Rs 46/kg. The ratio of the cheaper to the dearer rice is:",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "2:3"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "3:2"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "4:3"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "5:3"}
          ],
          "answer": "B",
          "explanation": "By alligation: (55-46):(46-40) = 9:6 = 3:2."
        },
        {
          "id": "q11",
          "type": "numerical",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Number Sense (Unit Digit)", "difficulty": "medium"},
          "text": "Enter the unit digit of 7 raised to the power 45.",
          "answer": 7,
          "tolerance": 0,
          "explanation": "The cycle 7, 9, 3, 1 repeats; 45 mod 4 = 1 gives 7."
        },
        {
          "id": "q12",
          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Algebraic Identities", "difficulty": "medium"},
          "text": "If a + b = 10 and ab = 21, then a^3 + b^3 equals:",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "340"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "370"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "400"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "430"}
          ],
          "answer": "B",
          "explanation": "(a+b)^3 - 3ab(a+b) = 1000 - 630 = 370."
        },
        {
          "id": "q13",
          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Partnership Business", "difficulty": "medium"},
          "text": "A, B and C invest Rs 25000, Rs 30000 and Rs 15000 for a year. Out of a profit of Rs 14000, C's share is:",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "Rs 2500"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "Rs 3000"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "Rs 3500"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "Rs 4200"}
          ],
          "answer": "B",
          "explanation": "Ratio 5:6:3; C gets 3/14 of 14000 = 3000."
        },
        {
          "id": "q14",
          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Mensuration (Wire Rebending)", "difficulty": "medium"},
          "text": "A wire bent into a square of side 22 cm is re-bent into a circle. The radius of the circle is: (use pi = 22/7)",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "7 cm"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "14 cm"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "21 cm"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "28 cm"}
          ],
          "answer": "B",
          "explanation": "Perimeter 88 = 2 x (22/7) x r gives r = 14."
        },
        {
          "id": "q15",
          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Circle (Tangents)", "difficulty": "medium"},
          "text": "The length of a tangent drawn from an external point to a circle of radius 7 cm is 24 cm. The distance of the point from the centre is:",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "24 cm"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "25 cm"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "26 cm"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "31 cm"}
          ],
          "answer": "B",
          "explanation": "sqrt(24^2 + 7^2) = 25."
        },
        {
          "id": "q16",
          "type": "single",
          "metadata": {"topic": "Graphs of Linear Equations", "difficulty": "medium"},
          "text": "The line 3x + 4y = 24 cuts the coordinate axes at A and B. The area of triangle OAB (O is the origin) is:",
          "options": [
            {"id": "A", "text": "20 sq units"},
            {"id": "B", "text": "24 sq units"},
            {"id": "C", "text": "28 sq units"},
            {"id": "D", "text": "48 sq units"}
          ],
          "answer": "B",
          "explanation": "Intercepts 8 and 6; area = (1/2) x 8 x 6 = 24."
        }
      ]
